In his Easter message, President Biden expresses gratitude to the White House Historical Association and the National Park Service for distributing commemorative eggs to vaccination sites across the country. He acknowledges that many people are still unable to celebrate the holiday with their loved ones due to the ongoing pandemic. However, he remains hopeful and emphasizes the importance of faith, hope, and love in rebuilding the nation. The President looks forward to a future Easter where the White House will once again host an Easter Egg Roll. He concludes by sending blessings to everyone and expressing his gratitude to the troops and the Easter Bunny.